Package: safetrain
Title: Reversible, ML-Safe Anonymization for Tabular Data
Description: Key-based anonymization of tabular data designed for GDPR-compliant
  machine learning workflows. Two transformation methods are provided: a PCA
  method (key-derived orthogonal rotation via HMAC-PRNG + QR decomposition,
  output has n-1 columns) and a cryptoencoder method (shallow n-to-n autoencoder
  with key-derived weight initialization and a key-derived orthogonal
  post-rotation, output has n columns with formal no-correspondence guarantees).
  All transformation parameters are derived from the secret key and never stored
  in plain text, so reversal requires both the key and the mapping. An optional
  (epsilon, delta)-differential privacy layer adds calibrated Gaussian noise to
  the cryptoencoder output, exploiting the bounded tanh output range for clean
  sensitivity analysis. A key-destruction mode permanently prevents recovery,
  converting the scheme from GDPR pseudonymization (Article 4(5)) to de facto
  anonymization (Recital 26) for use cases where auditability is not required.
Version: 0.2.0
